<!-- LANG:EN, title="How to join an existing group"-->

1 - If it's not already done, [[How to create an account|create an account]]

2 - Find the group you would like to join:

* either, if it's a public group, by [https://inventaire.io/network/groups/search searching it by name] or by [https://inventaire.io/network/groups/nearby location]
* or, if it's a private group, by visiting the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator URL] the group administrator should have sent you

3 - Once on the group page, click ''request to join the group'', and ''voilà''! You now just have to wait for the group administrator to validate your request.

[[File:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1596934/27707390-7449841c-5d15-11e7-9afe-0a89b17e35b0.png|request_to_join_group_en]]

4 - To make books available for exchanges in this group, you just need to [[How to add a book to my inventory|add books to your inventory]] and select the ''friends &amp; groups'' visibility option. Unfortunately, it's not yet possible to make a book visible to only certain friends or groups, [https://trello.com/c/hVawMbmt this feature is in the development waiting list]: feel welcome to [https://trello.com/c/hVawMbmt upvote] it to increase it's priority rank.

